Step 1. Calculate the Debt to Asset Ratio.
• Total liabilities: In the balance sheet, the only liabilities listed are current liabilities (Accounts Payable and Taxes Payable). Their sum is 302000.00 + 197821.72 = 499821.72.
• Total assets: 14890758.71.
• Debt to Asset Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Assets = 499821.72 / 14890758.71 ≈ 0.0336. Rounding to two decimal places gives 0.03.

Step 2. Calculate the Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio.
• Operating Cash Flow is given as –1182491.05.
• Net Income is given as 1390936.99.
• Ratio = Operating Cash Flow / Net Income = –1182491.05 / 1390936.99 ≈ –0.851.
Rounded to two decimal places, this is –0.85.

Thus, the solution in JSON format is:

{"solution": {"Debt to Asset Ratio": "0.03", "Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio": "-0.85"}}
